Title: United States v. Antonio Gordillo-Ramirez
HTMLtext:
Case: 09-50936     Document: 00511205798          Page: 1    Date Filed: 08/17/2010




           IN THE UNITED STATES COURT OF APPEALS
                    FOR THE FIFTH CIRCUIT  United States Court of Appeals
                                                    Fifth Circuit

                                                 FILED
                                                                           August 17, 2010
                                     No. 09-50936
                                  Conference Calendar                       Lyle W. Cayce
                                                                                 Clerk

UNITED STATES OF AMERICA,

                                                   Plaintiff-Appellee

v.

ANTONIO GORDILLO-RAMIREZ,

                                                   Defendant-Appellant


                    Appeal from the United States District Court
                         for the Western District of Texas
                             USDC No. 3:09-CR-1312-1


Before DAVIS, SMITH, and WIENER, Circuit Judges.
PER CURIAM:*
        The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Antonio Gordillo-
Ramirez (Gordillo) has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in
accordance with Anders v. California,
386 U.S. 738
 (1967). Gordillo has not filed
a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses
no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to
withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein,
and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5 TH C IR. R. 42.2.

       *
         Pursuant to 5TH CIR . R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not
be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5TH CIR .
R. 47.5.4.
